<subSubSection id="C37D65360C07F82A6DA09B54FAF5748E" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD836BD0C07F82A6DA09B54FD77776E" blockId="23.[192,1440,323,379]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6DA09B54FE9E774E" bold="true" box="[192,373,323,347]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6C1C9B54FE03774E" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" box="[380,488,323,347]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6C1C9B54FE03774E" box="[380,488,323,347]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the Neotropics, with species native to 
<collectingCountry id="F370762D0C07F82A69F39B54FB14774E" box="[1171,1279,323,347]" name="Grenada" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Grenada</collectingCountry>
and recently established on Hispaniola and 
<collectingCountry id="F370762D0C07F82A6F4F9B74FD72776E" box="[559,665,355,379]" name="Jamaica" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836BD0C07F82A6DA09BB4FACD740E" blockId="23.[192,1440,419,668]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6DA09BB4FEC177AE" bold="true" box="[192,298,419,443]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Larvae.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6C549BB4FE4B77AE" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" box="[308,416,419,443]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6C549BB4FE4B77AE" box="[308,416,419,443]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae were first diagnosed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B4C0C07F82A6E559BB4FBA777AE" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[821,1100,419,443]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="348 - 366" refId="ref50886" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. 1832. Notice sur l'entomologie de la Guyane Francais. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, (1 st Ser.) 1: 348 - 366, 447. [not seen]" type="journal article" year="1832">Lacordaire (1832: 364</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B4C0C07F82A693B9BB4FB0677AE" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[1115,1261,419,443]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="35 - 94" refId="ref50928" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. 1833. Esaai sur les Coleopteres de la Guiane Francaise. Novelles Annales du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 2: 35 - 94." type="journal article" year="1833">1833: 89-90</bibRefCitation>
) for “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A68579BB4FE8977CE" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Erotylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="surinamensis">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A68579BB4FE8977CE" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Erotylus surinamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B4C0C07F82A6C189BD4FDB577CE" author="Roberts, A. W. R." box="[376,606,451,475]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="245 - 285" refId="ref52201" refString="Roberts, A. W. R. 1958. On the taxonomy of the Erotylidae (Coleoptera), with special reference to the morphological characters of the larvae. II. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society London 110 (8): 245 - 285." type="journal article" year="1958">Roberts (1958: 281)</bibRefCitation>
briefly diagnosed larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6EC19BD4FB1577CE" authority="Crotch" authorityName="Crotch" box="[929,1278,451,475]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6EC19BD4FB4377CE" box="[929,1192,451,475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus meridionalis</emphasis>
Crotch
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A68569BD4FDC277EE" authority="Chevrolat. The" authorityName="Chevrolat. The" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotatus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A68569BD4FE8577EE" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus quadrinotatus</emphasis>
Chevrolat. The
</taxonomicName>
following diagnosis is based on the full description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A69CA9BF3FAA677EE" box="[1194,1357,483,507]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavicornis">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A69CA9BF3FAA677EE" box="[1194,1357,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">A. clavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B4C0C07F82A6D839814FDC0740E" author="Teixeira, E. P. &amp; S. A. Casari" box="[227,555,515,539]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="459 - 463" refId="ref52833" refString="Teixeira, E. P., and S. A. Casari. 1998. Description of larva and pupa of Aegithus clavicornis Linnaeus, 1758 (Coleoptera, Erotylidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 41 (2 - 4): 459 - 463." type="journal article" year="1998">Teixeira and Casari (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, and direct study of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6E7C9813FC66740E" box="[796,909,515,539]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lebasii">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6E7C9813FC66740E" box="[796,909,515,539]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">A. lebasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae from 
<collectingCountry id="F370762D0C07F82A69469814FB65740E" box="[1062,1166,515,539]" name="Jamaica" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="135C2A380C07F82A69FC9814FAF2740E" box="[1180,1305,515,539]" captionStart="Figure 42-45" captionStartId="22.[192,276,1838,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1430,209,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[207,1434,193,1811]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 42-45. Aegithus spp., male genitalia and larva. 42) A. clavicornis. 43) A. lebasii. 44-45) A. lebasii larva, lateral and dorsal view. Genitalic scale line = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405103/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Fig. 44-45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836BD0C07F82A6D909834FAF5748E" blockId="23.[192,1440,419,668]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Body elongate, with dark tergites, covered with spicules, scoli, and aristate or simple setae. Head setose, with short setiferous slender spines or tubercles. Antennal length about half head width. Tergites of T2-A8 dorsally with 3 long, branched scoli on each side. Abdominal epipleurites with single, large, branched scoli; urogomphi short, about as long as an abdominal segment. Spiracles annular.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D65360C07F82A6DA098D4FB15720E" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD836BD0C07F82A6DA098D4FD9D75AE" blockId="23.[192,1441,707,1052]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6DA098D4FED274CE" bold="true" box="[192,313,707,731]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. Generic limits, relationships, and placement of some taxa remain problematic within 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A684D98D4FA7774CE" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1325,1436,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Erotylini">Erotylini</taxonomicName>
. Likewise, the historical practice of identifying taxa based solely on written descriptions has led to many species being placed in incorrect genera or to the production of incorrect synonyms. Previously cited characters used to define genera and subgenera often vary among species presently assigned to these taxa and lead to descriptions like the one above. Considering these daunting problems, some species are difficult to confidently place in some genera (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6F829974FCA5756E" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" box="[738,846,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6F829974FCA5756E" box="[738,846,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6EE69974FC01756E" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" box="[902,1002,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Iphiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6EE69974FC01756E" box="[902,1002,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Iphiclus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and generic limits remain vague. A larger revisionary study with deep taxon sampling is needed to assess additional generic characters and resolve these tenuous generic limits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836BD0C07F82A6D9099D4FB15720E" blockId="23.[192,1441,707,1052]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6D9099D4FEB775CE" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" box="[240,348,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Aegithus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6D9099D4FEB775CE" box="[240,348,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Aegithus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D3E0C07F82A6CF599D4FE1275CE" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" box="[405,505,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Iphiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAAF0C07F82A6CF599D4FE1275CE" box="[405,505,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Iphiclus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are diverse mainland genera with few representatives naturally occurring in the West Indian fauna. Addressing mainland species to resolve generic limits is outside the scope of this work. Thus, traditional concepts of these genera and species placements were maintained.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
